        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-15T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="405" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856d.00/12–849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Consulate General at Batavia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-15T19:00:00-05:00">December 15, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>627. Your 979<note n="1" xml:id="d405fn1">December 8, 10 a. m., not
                        printed.</note> much appreciated. <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>
                    shipments will be marked with US flag and preparations now in process to insure
                    full propaganda capitalizing arrival <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> sums
                        <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>. Similar treatment will be accorded
                    ExImBank announcement extension credit to <gloss target="#t_USI1">USI</gloss>.
                    Technical missions and suggested visit fleet will be discussed by Cochran upon
                    arrival.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
